Constraint: FLOW TYPE CAPACITY

Context: For each instance of FlowEdge, a separate constraint for each TokenType allowed to flow.

Specification:

{

For each instance of flowTypeAllowed:

flowAmount <= flowCapacity;

}

Constraint: FLOW GROSS CAPACITY

Context: One constraint per instance of FlowEdge.

Specification:

{

Sum over flowTypeAllowed[*] ( flowAmount ) <= grossCapacity;

}

Constraint: FLOW BALANCE

Context: For each instance of FlowNode, a separate constraint for each TokenType produced, consumed, may flow in on an incoming FlowEdge, or may flow out on an outgoing FlowEdge.

Specification:

{

Form a set of TokenType instances as the union of:

- FlowNode.production.tokenType[1..*]

- FlowNode.consumption.tokenType[1..*]

- FlowNode.incomingFlowEdge[*].flowTypeAllowed[*]

- FlowNode.outgoingFlowEdge[*].flowTypeAllowed[*].

For each TokenType instance `t' in that set:

supply = FlowNode.production.tokenQuantity (of type t);

demand = FlowNode.consumption.tokenQuantity (of type t);

flow_in = Sum( FlowNode.incomingFlowEdge[*].flowAmount (of type t) );

flow_out = Sum( FlowNode.outgoingFlowEdge[*].flowAmount (of type t) );

supply + flow_in == demand + flow_out;

}

Constraint: FLOW NON-NEGATIVITY

Context: For each instance of FlowEdge, a separate constraint for each TokenType allowed to flow.

Specification:

{

For each instance of flowTypeAllowed:

flowAmount >= 0;

}

Routing Control (Execution):

Anytime there are multiple outgoing edges, a decision needs to be made on which edge the token is placed.

In flow networks, passive control is implemented by proportion; in process networks, by probability (stochastic proportion?)
